<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Textbook">Textbook</span></h2>
<p>I have purchased the textbook and found it to be a useful supplement to the course materials.  It would be helpful if for each topic, corresponding chapters or sections in the textbook could be identified.</p>
<p>Answer: If you go on the course page to the <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://class.coursera.org/pgm-2012-002/wiki/view?page=LectureSlides">lecture slides</a>, you'll find which parts of the book correspond with the lectures.</p>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Class_Mechanics">Class Mechanics</span></h2>
<p>I received no mail to tell me abou the start of the class; I can find no information on this site to tell me when the next class takes place and no way to provide feedback or contact the course organiser other than this page ...Helpppp!!</p>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Programming_Assignments">Programming Assignments</span></h2>
<p>Please, post well commented vectorized solutions at the end of the course. Thank you!</p>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Calculations">Calculations</span></h2>
<p>Please provide more examples of the calculations for all the reasoning types: Causal, Evidential, and Inter-causal. Seems like these calculations are extremely important for this class, but the professor assume the ability to calculate these and gives no complete explanation how.</p>

